		<h2>CSS Reusability Demonstration</h2>
		<div class="note-grid">
			<div class="note-item">
				<h3>Same CSS, Different Content</h3>
				<p>This page uses the exact same CSS file as all_together.html but with completely different content, demonstrating the power of semantic HTML and well-structured CSS.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="note-item">
				<h3>Maintainable Code</h3>
				<p>By separating content from presentation, you can easily update the design of multiple pages by modifying just one CSS file.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="note-item">
				<h3>Consistent Design</h3>
				<p>Using the same CSS ensures visual consistency across different pages while allowing for unique content on each page.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="note-item">
				<h3>Scalable Architecture</h3>
				<p>This approach scales well for larger websites where you need consistent styling across many different pages and content types.</p>
			</div>
